`zipDelayError` completes empty in case any source completes without value. `...DelayError` means that in case several Monos result in error, their exceptions are combined. In contrast `zip` would return error from the first failed `Mono`. 

To achieve mentioned logic you would need to handle these errors on the `proxy.getImage` level and in case of `NOT FOUND` return some default value.

```
Mono&lt;Image&gt; getImage(String domain, String id) {
    return proxy.getImage(domain, id)
            .onErrorResume(e -&gt; {
                if (NOT FOUND) {
                    // return default value
                    return Mono.just(&lt;default image&gt;)
                } esle if (INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR) {
                    // return custom error
                    return Mono.error(new CustomException(INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR))
                }

                // return original error
                return Mono.error(e);
            });
}
```

