The problem is with this code:
```
t = 1/t;
double[][] tValues = {{1,t,t*t,t*t*t}};
...
for (double i = t; i &lt; 1; i+=t) {
  ...
}
```

That `tValues` matrix is a variable, it needs to be _recomputed_ every time you compute a point for a new `t` value. And that `t` value should definitely not be stored at the object level, and _super definitely_ not get inverted any time you run your draw function. As your loop variable, keep it local to your `for` loop. At best, store your `step` size at the object level.

```
beginDrawing(); // whatever is your API&#39;s equivalent of this

double[][] xVal, yVal;
for(double t=0, step=0.01; t&lt;1.0; t+=step) {
  double[][] tValues = {{1,t,t*t,t*t*t}};

  // get the x coordinate **for this t value**
  xVal = Util.matrixMultiplication(tValues, multiX);

  // get the y coordinate **for this t value**
  yVal = Util.matrixMultiplication(tValues, multiY);

  addVertex(xVal[0][0], yVal[0][0]);  // or equivalent
}

endDrawing();  // or equivalent
```

